---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

// ── Build a static calendar for the next few months marking meeting days ──
// City: 2nd & 4th Mondays. County: 1st & 3rd Mondays.
// (Holiday bumps to Tuesday are noted in text, not auto-computed.)
const MONTHS = ["January","February","March","April","May","June","July","August","September","October","November","December"];
const DOW = ["S","M","T","W","T","F","S"];

function nthMondays(year, month) {
  // returns { mondays: [day numbers in order] }
  const mondays = [];
  const daysInMonth = new Date(year, month + 1, 0).getDate();
  for (let d = 1; d <= daysInMonth; d++) {
    if (new Date(year, month, d).getDay() === 1) mondays.push(d);
  }
  return mondays;
}

function buildMonth(year, month) {
  const mondays = nthMondays(year, month);
  const county = [mondays[0], mondays[2]].filter(Boolean);   // 1st & 3rd
  const city = [mondays[1], mondays[3]].filter(Boolean);     // 2nd & 4th
  const firstDow = new Date(year, month, 1).getDay();
  const daysInMonth = new Date(year, month + 1, 0).getDate();
  const cells = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < firstDow; i++) cells.push(null);
  for (let d = 1; d <= daysInMonth; d++) cells.push(d);
  return { name: MONTHS[month], year, cells, county, city };
}

const now = new Date();
const calendars = [0, 1, 2].map(offset => {
  const dt = new Date(now.getFullYear(), now.getMonth() + offset, 1);
  return buildMonth(dt.getFullYear(), dt.getMonth());
});
---

<Layout title="When and Where to Show Up">
  <div class="content">
    <span class="card-tag" style="background: rgba(42, 157, 143, 0.2); color: #2A9D8F;">Act</span>
    <h1>When and Where to Show Up</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 1.15rem;">
      A signature is a number. A neighbor at the podium is a problem the council has to answer. These two bodies hold the Flock contracts. Their meetings are public, and you have the right to speak. Here's when, where, and how.
    </p>

    <h2>The Next Few Months</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted);">
      County meetings (1st &amp; 3rd Mondays) are solid red. City meetings (2nd &amp; 4th Mondays) are outlined. Holidays bump a meeting to the next day, so always confirm on the official agenda.
    </p>

    <div class="stat-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));">
      {calendars.map(cal => (
        <div class="cal">
          <div class="cal-title">{cal.name} {cal.year}</div>
          <div class="cal-grid">
            {DOW.map(d => <div class="cal-dow">{d}</div>)}
            {cal.cells.map(day => {
              if (day === null) return <div class="cal-day empty">.</div>;
              if (cal.county.includes(day)) return <div class="cal-day meeting">{day}</div>;
              if (cal.city.includes(day)) return <div class="cal-day meeting-alt">{day}</div>;
              return <div class="cal-day">{day}</div>;
            })}
          </div>
          <div class="cal-legend">
            <span><span class="cal-swatch" style="background: var(--color-accent);"></span> County</span>
            <span><span class="cal-swatch" style="border: 2px solid var(--color-accent);"></span> City</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2>Safford City Council</h2>
    <p>Holds the contract for Safford PD's cameras.</p>
    <div class="card">
      <ul class="card-specifics">
        <li><strong>When:</strong> Usually the 2nd and 4th Monday of the month at 6:00 PM. If that Monday is a holiday, it moves to the next Tuesday. Some months vary, so check the agenda before you go.</li>
        <li><strong>Where:</strong> Safford Library Program Room, 808 S. 7th Ave., Safford, AZ 85546</li>
        <li><strong>Watch live:</strong> City of Safford YouTube channel</li>
        <li><strong>Agendas:</strong> cityofsafford.us &rarr; Agenda Center</li>
        <li><strong>Public comment:</strong> meetings include a "Citizen Comments on Non-Agenda Items" period &mdash; that's your slot</li>
      </ul>
      <a href={`${base}safford-city-council.ics`} class="btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;" download>Add City Council to Calendar</a>
    </div>

    <h2>Graham County Board of Supervisors</h2>
    <p>Holds the contract for the Sheriff's Office cameras.</p>
    <div class="card">
      <ul class="card-specifics">
        <li><strong>When:</strong> The 1st and 3rd Monday of every month. If that Monday is a holiday, it moves to Tuesday.</li>
        <li><strong>Where:</strong> Graham County General Services Building, Assembly Room, 921 W. Thatcher Blvd., Safford, AZ 85546</li>
        <li><strong>Agendas &amp; minutes:</strong> graham.az.gov &rarr; Meetings and Agendas</li>
        <li><strong>Questions / accommodations:</strong> Board of Supervisors office, 928-428-3250</li>
      </ul>
      <a href={`${base}graham-county-supervisors.ics`} class="btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;" download>Add Board of Supervisors to Calendar</a>
    </div>

    <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted);">
      The calendar files set up a recurring reminder for every 1st/3rd or 2nd/4th Monday. They can't know which Mondays are holidays, so the reminder itself tells you to confirm the date on the official agenda. Always confirm before you go &mdash; we'd rather you not drive down to a locked door. If you spot a meeting listed here that has changed, tell us and we'll fix it.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Give Public Comment</h2>
    <p>
      You don't need to be a lawyer or a regular. You get a few minutes. Here's how to use them.
    </p>
    <div class="card">
      <ul class="card-specifics">
        <li><strong>Sign up.</strong> Most meetings have a sign-in sheet or card for public comment. Get there a few minutes early and put your name down.</li>
        <li><strong>Keep it to one ask.</strong> "Please request our Flock network audit and review the contract before it renews." One clear request lands harder than five.</li>
        <li><strong>Bring receipts, not vibes.</strong> Name the Scottsdale searches, the Glendale slur, the Tempe protest searches. Real Arizona facts, not "I heard."</li>
        <li><strong>Stay calm and short.</strong> You're talking to the 50 people in the room and the camera, not just the council. Flat and factual wins.</li>
        <li><strong>You're allowed to be nervous.</strong> Read it off a card if you need to. Showing up is most of the work.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>A Two-Minute Script You Can Read</h2>
    <blockquote>
      My name is ___ and I live in ___. The Flock cameras on our roads feed a national network that thousands of outside agencies can search. On that same network, one Phoenix-area department ran over twelve thousand searches, an officer logged an ethnic slur as a reason, and Arizona agencies used it to track people at protests. I'm not asking our police to stop solving crimes. I'm asking this body to request our network audit and hold a public hearing before the Flock contract is renewed. Show us who is watching. Thank you.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="cta-banner">
      <h3>Before You Go, Bring the Paper</h3>
      <p>Walk in with the records request already filed and the petition numbers in hand. Both make your two minutes hit harder.</p>
      <a href={`${base}records/`} class="btn">Records Request</a>
      <a href={`${base}petition/`} class="btn btn-outline">Sign the Petition</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
